Telson
: Vesicle slightly elongate, not laterally compressed, width similar to metasoma V width; anterodorsal lateral lobes reduced or absent; lateral and ventral surfaces granular (

T. translucidus

) or smooth (

T. lacrau

), with distinct ventromedian carina; subaculear tubercle well developed, spinoid.
